{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Bi9rAGqvhVKHodC2QKdYyZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both tests pass. Here's what was done and why:\n\n**Root cause:** At exactly 2 QPS input with a 2 r/s nginx limit and `burst=2`, the token bucket refills at the same rate tokens are consumed — zero rejections. The limit needed to be set lower than the test rate to actually trigger throttling.\n\n**Configuration applied** (annotation on `rate-api` ingress only):\n\n| Annotation | Value | Effect |\n|---|---|---|\n| `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps` | `1` | 1 request/second steady-state rate |\n| `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-burst-multiplier` | `1` | burst = 1×1 = 1 (tightest allowed) |\n\nWith rate=1 r/s and burst=1, the bucket fills halfway between each 0.5 s request. Requests alternate between \"bucket just enough\" and \"bucket still recovering,\" producing the observed pass/reject/pass/reject… pattern — 4 of 10 rejected with 503. The `rate-health` ingress has no rate-limiting annotations and returns 200 on every request."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":409,"cache_read_input_tokens":53687,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":409},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7d2f895-e84c-4374-8aa1-339424b20979","uuid":"24ec757e-63b7-4db0-8a51-67e859a072fe","request_id":"req_011CcMULEkCLK4re2415D5u4"}
